ion workshop has been selected by August 10th  If you are interested in being a presenter this year  please fill out our online form  We are looking for workshops that provide fresh  take away  teaching ideas  and presentations on successful implementation of curriculum  technology and programs  Presentations and resource links will be shared post conference on our conference website  Workshops and presentations are 50 minutes in length  Presenters receive 15 CEUs for each topic  Topics of interest for teachers and administrators in grades 3   8 include  STEM Integration Cybersecurity competitions Coding Coding Apps Day of Code Robotics Maker Fairs Special Education STEM Legos Keva planks  etc  NETiquette online safety cyberbullying STEAM Digital Storytelling Math Sciences Engineering Computer Science Data Visualization Helpful Apps Programs Teacher resources Rural District challenges 2D 3D Printing Your ideas are welcome  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 